# Signed plugin source and manifest files must have stable working-tree bytes
# across platforms. Plugin manifest verification hashes the raw file bytes
# (sha256 of fs.readFileSync), so a CRLF checkout (e.g. Windows with
# core.autocrlf=true) would change the bytes and break hash verification,
# causing plugins to be rejected at load. Force LF for these signed files.
plugins/**/*.js text eol=lf
plugins/**/*.json text eol=lf
